_"By the way, for your specific example, you can set the xmlns attributes using the DOM API directly by using selection.node() to retrieve the first Element in the selection."_

I'll share the code I used for workaround that @jasondavies describes:

```
var svg = d3.select("body").append("svg")

svg.node().setAttributeNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/", "xmlns", "http://www.w3.org/2000/svg");

svg.node().setAttributeNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/", "xmlns:xlink", "http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink");
```

In case it's helpful for future search engine visitors, here's the [stackoverflow question](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/18092976/is-it-possible-to-import-svg-shapes-in-d3-js) that led me here, along with a  [bl.ock](http://bl.ocks.org/explunit/5988971) that shows an example of these attributes hard-coded in an `<svg>` tag.
